The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                               IN THE CITY
                  
	 Mohun Bagan, East Bengal and Chirag United will play all of their I-League home matches at the Salt Lake Stadium till October 25. The decision was taken after AIFF representative Anil Kamath visited the Salt Lake Stadium and the Howrah Stadium on Tuesday along with representatives of the three clubs. The trios matches from October 26 onwards might be shifted to the Barasat Stadium.       
	Meanwhile, East Bengal explained the reasons behind the expulsion of Jan Berger, Sebastien Omar and Edmilson Marques to sponsor United Breweries in a meeting on Tuesday.                
	 The Cricket Association of Bengal (CAB) has decided to advance the S.K. Acharya Challenger Trophy, which was scheduled to be held in the second week of October, and will now be held from October 1-8. Four teams will be participating in this years meet and the winners will be decided on a round-robin league basis. Former Bengal captain and ex-ICL player Deep Dasgupta is set to become the captain of one of the teams, revealed sources.                                                                                                                                                                       
